                             <div class="col-lg-7 comment-bottom w3pvt_mail_grid_right">
                            <p>Veterinary Science is a branch of science that concerns with diagnosis, treatment and curing of diseases in birds and animals. The subject involves the study of animal physiology and various treatment and prevention schemes undertaken to block diseases among animals. The basic principles of veterinary science and animal husbandry are similar as human medical sciences. The difference is in the variation of jobs; a veterinary doctor has many responsibilities than that of a general physician or a human surgeon. Students while studying B.V.Sc. Veterinary Science and A. H. not only take care of animal health but also facilitate scientific breeding and handling of livestock.Vets give treatment to the animals for their healthy living. Major part of their work also involves performing surgery in cases where internal parts of animals and birds are injured.</p>
